The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, June 16, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, June 15: Sterlite Industries has posted a 17.58 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 197.14 crore in 2003-04 compared with Rs 167.66 crore in the previous fiscal. The board has recommended a 60 per cent dividend (Rs 3 per share) for 2003-04 on the expanded equity after the bonus issue. Total income increased to Rs 3,086.31 crore in 2003-04 from Rs 2,225.91 crore in 2002-03.																								 Calcutta, June 15: Berger Paints India Limited today recommended a final dividend of 30 per cent for 2003-04 after reporting a profit before tax of over Rs 61 crore. The companys shareholders also approved a proposal at an extra-ordinary general meeting by which its bonus shares would be treated as pari passu in all respect, including dividend.																								 Mumbai, June 15: Deutsche Bank India has reported a 60 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 272.6 crore in 2003-04 compared with Rs 170.6 crore in the previous financial year. Total income increased by 31 per cent to Rs 905.6 crore (Rs 692.8 crore).																								 Mumbai, June 15: Rallis India Ltd has posted a net profit of Rs 25.55 crore in 2003-04 against a loss of Rs 77.27 crore in 2002-03. The board has not recommended any dividend for the year due to carry-forward losses, a company release said.																								 New Delhi, June 15: Buoyed by a 17.26 per cent export growth in 2003-04, the government is likely to set this fiscals export growth target at around a stiff 12 per cent, same as last year.
